1041
00:52:35,777 --> 00:52:37,237
Everything was through my job.

1042
00:52:37,737 --> 00:52:38,864
I see.

1043
00:52:38,947 --> 00:52:41,908
- It's like pseudo love.
- I see.

1044
00:52:41,992 --> 00:52:45,203
I think it's different
from having your emotions stirred.

1045
00:52:45,287 --> 00:52:46,246
Yeah.

1046
00:52:46,329 --> 00:52:48,415
But you're talking properly.

1047
00:52:48,498 --> 00:52:50,500
- Now I am.
- Yeah.

1048
00:52:51,001 --> 00:52:53,003
Since time is limited.

1049
00:52:53,712 --> 00:52:54,754
That's true.

1050
00:52:55,839 --> 00:52:56,965
You know what?

1051
00:52:57,549 --> 00:53:00,135
- I go by the name Tohko Asai.
- Tohko Asai?

1052
00:53:00,218 --> 00:53:01,970
- But…
- Yeah?

1053
00:53:02,053 --> 00:53:05,348
My real name is Riko.

1054
00:53:05,432 --> 00:53:06,308
Oh!

1055
00:53:06,391 --> 00:53:10,187
- You got a stage name for your job?
- Yeah.

1056
00:53:10,270 --> 00:53:12,272
- What's this?
- There are people like that.

1057
00:53:12,355 --> 00:53:14,900
She's giving away her name.
It's like <i>Spirited Away.</i>

1058
00:53:15,400 --> 00:53:16,985
I'm told I look like a Riko.

1059
00:53:17,068 --> 00:53:18,236
It fits you perfectly.

1060
00:53:18,320 --> 00:53:19,487
- Right?
- Yeah.

1061
00:53:25,118 --> 00:53:26,203
Delicious, isn't it?

1062
00:53:28,330 --> 00:53:29,164
It is.

1063
00:53:31,166 --> 00:53:34,336
- Ta-da!
- What is it?

1064
00:53:34,419 --> 00:53:36,796
- Since you decorate your guidebook…
- Yeah.

1065
00:53:38,548 --> 00:53:40,133
- Can I take a look?
- Yeah.

1066
00:53:40,217 --> 00:53:41,927
MIMI, 20, PART-TIME WORKER

1067
00:53:42,010 --> 00:53:45,639
- What is it?
- I chose French-ish stickers.

1068
00:53:45,722 --> 00:53:47,140
Wow. Thank you!

1069
00:53:47,224 --> 00:53:51,895
- You can make your guidebook fancier.
- You always give me presents.

1070
00:53:51,978 --> 00:53:53,063
Well…

1071
00:53:54,481 --> 00:53:55,315
I mean…

1072
00:53:55,815 --> 00:53:57,734
It's nothing much.

1073
00:53:57,817 --> 00:53:59,152
I really appreciate it.

1074
00:53:59,236 --> 00:54:02,239
You always give me gifts.

1075
00:54:02,322 --> 00:54:03,406
You're so kind.

1076
00:54:04,282 --> 00:54:06,159
No, "kind" isn't the right word.

1077
00:54:06,243 --> 00:54:07,911
You're romantic.

1078
00:54:08,787 --> 00:54:11,456
After we finish our meal,

1079
00:54:13,083 --> 00:54:14,334
can we take a walk?

1080
00:54:14,417 --> 00:54:15,252
Of course.

1081
00:54:30,225 --> 00:54:31,601
- Hi.
- Hey.

1082
00:54:31,685 --> 00:54:33,603
- It's you, Atsushi.
- Hey.

1083
00:54:33,687 --> 00:54:35,480
- Come on in.
- Thanks.

1084
00:54:36,273 --> 00:54:39,192
- I wanted to chat with you.
- Sure.

1085
00:54:39,276 --> 00:54:43,488
- So, you've switched over to Kanaka?
- Well, yeah.

1086
00:54:43,571 --> 00:54:46,157
Kanaka is the only one for me.

1087
00:54:46,241 --> 00:54:48,201
- It's like that?
- Yeah.

1088
00:54:48,285 --> 00:54:49,494
Don't say "switch over."

1089
00:54:50,328 --> 00:54:51,538
He's here to check.

1090
00:54:51,621 --> 00:54:53,581
- Sho liked Mimi at first.
- Right.

1091
00:54:53,665 --> 00:54:55,709
You seem so confident.

1092
00:54:55,792 --> 00:54:58,837
- I'm not confident at all.
- Really?

1093
00:54:58,920 --> 00:55:01,464
I'm constantly thinking about
how to make her fall for me.

1094
00:55:02,132 --> 00:55:05,010
- I can't sleep.
- But you've got good vibes, right?

1095
00:55:05,093 --> 00:55:07,178
I think we've got good vibes.

1096
00:55:07,262 --> 00:55:10,098
But I haven't held hands
with her like you have.

1097
00:55:11,224 --> 00:55:12,892
I haven't done any of that stuff.

1098
00:55:13,393 --> 00:55:15,228
I still feel some distance between us.

1099
00:55:15,312 --> 00:55:17,314
- You haven't hugged her?
- No hugging.

1100
00:55:17,814 --> 00:55:19,816
I don't know her true feelings.

1101
00:55:19,899 --> 00:55:20,942
I see.

1102
00:55:21,026 --> 00:55:25,030
I haven't really asked her though.
I don't really want to ask.

1103
00:55:25,530 --> 00:55:28,033
I haven't asked her, but I am curious.

1104
00:55:28,116 --> 00:55:31,328
You don't have to ask her,
but maybe you should tell her.

1105
00:55:31,411 --> 00:55:32,746
Tell her your feelings.

1106
00:55:32,829 --> 00:55:35,332
- Maybe I'll do that tomorrow.
- Yeah.

1107
00:55:36,374 --> 00:55:38,793
Since we're in Nice,
can we sit on the blue chairs?

1108
00:55:38,877 --> 00:55:39,711
Of course!

1109
00:55:40,211 --> 00:55:41,421
It's the sea.

1110
00:55:42,172 --> 00:55:43,882
- The ocean!
- Let's sit.

1111
00:55:44,382 --> 00:55:45,508
- Here?
- Yeah.

1112
00:55:45,592 --> 00:55:46,426
Can I sit?

1113
00:55:47,093 --> 00:55:49,095
- Phew.
- Phew.

1114
00:55:50,013 --> 00:55:51,973
- Wow.
- I've been wanting to do this.

1115
00:55:52,057 --> 00:55:53,850
But it's pitch dark.

1116
00:55:53,933 --> 00:55:55,185
It's dark, but it's nice.

1117
00:55:55,268 --> 00:55:58,563
It's like the sea
and the sky are connected.

1118
00:55:58,646 --> 00:56:00,482
So it looks like it's all the ocean.

1119
00:56:02,025 --> 00:56:03,401
It feels so good.

1120
00:56:03,485 --> 00:56:04,402
Nice.

1121
00:56:05,695 --> 00:56:07,989
Did you go up there already?

1122
00:56:08,490 --> 00:56:10,658
- That one.
- Jumanji? Not yet.

1123
00:56:10,742 --> 00:56:13,161
They light it up like that.

1124
00:56:13,244 --> 00:56:14,746
But it closes at 6:00 p.m.

1125
00:56:15,372 --> 00:56:16,206
So yesterday,

1126
00:56:16,706 --> 00:56:19,084
because I wanted to bring you there,

1127
00:56:19,584 --> 00:56:23,838
I checked where Jumanji is,
and how we would get there.

1128
00:56:23,922 --> 00:56:25,048
Wow!

1129
00:56:25,882 --> 00:56:26,716
Yeah.

1130
00:56:27,217 --> 00:56:30,387
The entrance actually isn't on this map.

1131
00:56:30,470 --> 00:56:33,890
- What?
- That's why I had to go check myself.

1132
00:56:33,973 --> 00:56:37,060
- I'm so sorry.
- I don't want you to apologize.

1133
00:56:37,143 --> 00:56:39,270
I'm so sorry we couldn't go there.

1134
00:56:39,354 --> 00:56:40,980
What I want to say is,

1135
00:56:41,481 --> 00:56:45,318
the view of Nice
from up there is spectacular.

1136
00:56:45,860 --> 00:56:51,616
I'm hoping we can go there
on one of our remaining days.

1137
00:56:51,699 --> 00:56:52,742
I wanna go too.

1138
00:56:52,826 --> 00:56:55,495
- We need to go parachuting too.
- Yeah.

1139
00:56:55,578 --> 00:56:59,249
The view from up there is incredible,
so I wanna take you there.

1140
00:56:59,332 --> 00:57:00,458
- Yeah.
- That, and…

1141
00:57:01,459 --> 00:57:03,545
Huh? What is it?

1142
00:57:04,462 --> 00:57:06,923
I'd like to spend the day
with you tomorrow.

1143
00:57:09,092 --> 00:57:10,468
Will you join me?

1144
00:57:11,302 --> 00:57:12,512
Of course.

1145
00:57:13,805 --> 00:57:14,764
For you.

1146
00:57:14,848 --> 00:57:16,558
Thank you.

1147
00:57:17,058 --> 00:57:18,435
- Can I look?
- Sure.

1148
00:57:25,233 --> 00:57:26,943
We meet at Nice-Ville station.

1149
00:57:28,236 --> 00:57:30,155
- Oh! Can I read this too?
- Sure.

1150
00:57:31,322 --> 00:57:34,826
I ENJOYED SPENDING TIME WITH YOU TODAY.
LET'S MAKE TOMORROW THE BEST DAY!

1151
00:57:34,909 --> 00:57:36,161
Thank you!

1152
00:57:36,661 --> 00:57:39,247
Is there anything I should know?
How should I dress?

1153
00:57:39,330 --> 00:57:41,207
- We might walk a lot.
- Walk a lot?

1154
00:57:41,291 --> 00:57:43,334
We'll leave France on foot.

1155
00:57:43,418 --> 00:57:45,336
What? We'll leave France?

1156
00:57:45,837 --> 00:57:47,172
What? I don't get it.

1157
00:57:47,255 --> 00:57:49,716
You'll be fine
if you're not in high heels.

1158
00:57:49,799 --> 00:57:51,843
No high heels? Okay.

1159
00:57:51,926 --> 00:57:53,344
I'm looking forward to this.

1160
00:57:53,428 --> 00:57:55,054
I'm excited too.

1161
00:57:55,680 --> 00:57:56,764
Tomorrow?

1162
00:57:57,599 --> 00:57:59,267
I think Aru is…

1163
00:57:59,350 --> 00:58:01,895
- Oh!
- He has the Wish Letter.

1164
00:58:01,978 --> 00:58:04,397
He passed it to Mimi, then?

1165
00:58:04,481 --> 00:58:06,774
- I think he passed it to her.
- Oh.

1166
00:58:07,275 --> 00:58:10,945
I met Maho at Margaux this morning.

1167
00:58:11,029 --> 00:58:13,865
You got the Wish Letter from her?

1168
00:58:13,948 --> 00:58:15,492
- No.
- Huh?

1169
00:58:15,992 --> 00:58:17,702
Then who got it?

1170
00:58:17,785 --> 00:58:22,957
- Maho was waiting downstairs just now.
- What?

1171
00:58:23,041 --> 00:58:25,543
So, what will you do tomorrow?

1172
00:58:25,627 --> 00:58:29,797
- You like Mimi.
- Yeah.

1173
00:58:29,881 --> 00:58:31,466
Will you meet anybody else?

1174
00:58:31,549 --> 00:58:33,551
That's the thing.

1175
00:58:35,053 --> 00:58:36,596
I'm still thinking.

1176
00:58:36,679 --> 00:58:38,181
Thank you.

1177
00:58:38,264 --> 00:58:40,099
- I'll see you tomorrow.
- Yeah.

1178
00:58:40,725 --> 00:58:41,601
Thanks.

1179
00:58:42,435 --> 00:58:44,270
See you tomorrow.

1180
00:58:44,354 --> 00:58:46,314
- It's in a few hours.
- Okay.

1181
00:58:46,397 --> 00:58:47,607
- Bye.
- Good night.

1182
00:58:47,690 --> 00:58:49,817
Good night!

1183
00:59:03,122 --> 00:59:04,123
Hey.

1184
00:59:04,207 --> 00:59:05,667
- Huh?
- What?

1185
00:59:05,750 --> 00:59:07,627
- Hi.
- Hi.

1186
00:59:08,419 --> 00:59:10,380
- What are you doing?
- Huh?

1187
00:59:11,589 --> 00:59:13,299
- Are you here to see me?
- No.

1188
00:59:13,383 --> 00:59:15,176
No, right? Oh, okay. You startled me.

1189
00:59:18,721 --> 00:59:19,973
He's just too cute.

1190
00:59:20,056 --> 00:59:22,809
I like how Maho reacts.

1191
00:59:22,892 --> 00:59:24,435
- I'd better go, right?
- Yeah.

1192
00:59:24,519 --> 00:59:25,353
Sorry.

1193
00:59:25,937 --> 00:59:27,814
- Good luck.
- Thanks.

1194
00:59:27,897 --> 00:59:28,982
Good night.

1195
00:59:30,775 --> 00:59:32,151
- That was delicious.
- Yeah.

1196
00:59:32,235 --> 00:59:33,194
What should we do?

1197
00:59:33,278 --> 00:59:35,238
Do you wanna go to Place Masséna?

1198
00:59:35,738 --> 00:59:36,573
Sure.

1199
00:59:42,495 --> 00:59:45,540
The fresh air will sober us up.

1200
00:59:46,040 --> 00:59:47,125
I'm not drunk.

1201
00:59:48,626 --> 00:59:49,627
It's cold.

1202
00:59:50,795 --> 00:59:53,715
- I'm cold.
- It gets chilly at night.

1203
00:59:56,384 --> 00:59:58,261
- So today…
- Yeah?

1204
01:00:07,729 --> 01:00:09,856
- So today…
- Yeah?

1205
01:00:11,357 --> 01:00:12,942
I had a goal in mind.

1206
01:00:13,860 --> 01:00:14,986
What was it?

1207
01:00:30,793 --> 01:00:32,253
I want to hold hands.

1208
01:00:34,964 --> 01:00:35,840
Here.

1209
01:00:39,385 --> 01:00:40,553
Oh, wow.

1210
01:00:48,603 --> 01:00:49,687
Thank you.

1211
01:00:50,313 --> 01:00:51,189
No problem.

1212
01:01:20,843 --> 01:01:21,678
Take a seat.

1213
01:01:22,595 --> 01:01:23,846
Thank you.

1214
01:01:31,354 --> 01:01:33,606
- So today…
- Yeah?

1215
01:01:37,610 --> 01:01:43,616
- I was able to tell you my feelings.
- Yeah.

1216
01:01:44,117 --> 01:01:45,493
But I want you

1217
01:01:46,744 --> 01:01:49,497
to find your true love.

1218
01:01:50,248 --> 01:01:51,958
- Yeah.
- So…

1219
01:01:52,792 --> 01:01:53,626
But

1220
01:01:54,794 --> 01:01:57,547
I want you to keep me in mind as well.

1221
01:01:58,798 --> 01:01:59,632
Yeah.

1222
01:02:00,299 --> 01:02:01,259
Okay.

1223
01:02:04,929 --> 01:02:06,222
Can we…

1224
01:02:08,182 --> 01:02:09,100
Never mind.

1225
01:02:11,728 --> 01:02:12,562
Hmm?

1226
01:02:14,188 --> 01:02:16,566
Can we hold hands again?

1227
01:02:29,829 --> 01:02:30,955
Thank you.

1228
01:02:31,622 --> 01:02:32,665
No problem.

1229
01:02:36,461 --> 01:02:37,920
I had fun.

1230
01:02:38,838 --> 01:02:40,298
We still have parachuting.

1231
01:02:42,383 --> 01:02:43,259
Yeah.

1232
01:02:47,597 --> 01:02:51,809
- Wow, that was nice!
- Oh, wow.

1233
01:02:51,893 --> 01:02:54,604
- Tohko tried so hard.
- She said things clearly.

1234
01:02:54,687 --> 01:02:58,274
We thought she would use
the tactics she learned from Mimi.

1235
01:02:58,357 --> 01:03:00,485
But she said, "I had a goal in mind."

1236
01:03:00,568 --> 01:03:02,069
She went her own way.

1237
01:03:02,153 --> 01:03:03,029
She was original.

1238
01:03:03,112 --> 01:03:07,116
I would be scared
if a girl said, "I had a goal in mind."

1239
01:03:07,200 --> 01:03:09,577
It would make
the guy nervous, wouldn't it?

1240
01:03:09,660 --> 01:03:10,995
Of course.

1241
01:03:11,078 --> 01:03:13,623
<i>If I were Yudai, I would think,</i>

1242
01:03:13,706 --> 01:03:15,750
<i>"Do I need to give her an answer today?"</i>

1243
01:03:15,833 --> 01:03:17,877
He used parachuting
as an escape a few times.

1244
01:03:18,377 --> 01:03:21,672
- Don't call it an escape.
- It's like, "Do I have to say it now?"

1245
01:03:21,756 --> 01:03:23,758
I definitely can't wait that long.

1246
01:03:23,841 --> 01:03:25,843
- I think Yudai is amazing.
- Yeah.

1247
01:03:25,927 --> 01:03:28,179
I'd say things like,
"Do you wanna hold hands?"

1248
01:03:28,262 --> 01:03:31,808
I don't think I could stand it.
I would start blabbering.

1249
01:03:31,891 --> 01:03:32,725
I know!

1250
01:03:32,809 --> 01:03:35,019
"Look! Isn't that beautiful?"

1251
01:03:35,520 --> 01:03:38,105
- "That looks tasty."
- "I wanna go there."

1252
01:03:38,189 --> 01:03:42,944
Tohko mentioned during dinner
that her real name is Riko.

1253
01:03:43,027 --> 01:03:45,863
<i>Does she want him to call her Riko?</i>

1254
01:03:45,947 --> 01:03:48,032
I took it as her
disclosing a secret to him.

1255
01:03:48,115 --> 01:03:50,326
- Maybe.
- She's not asking him to call her Riko?

1256
01:03:50,409 --> 01:03:53,996
That might be part of it,
but she doesn't expect it for now.

1257
01:03:54,080 --> 01:03:57,250
Maybe she wanted to feel closer to him.

1258
01:03:58,167 --> 01:04:01,629
- She would feel closer to him.
- Yeah.

1259
01:04:01,712 --> 01:04:03,881
For me, it was Mimi.

1260
01:04:03,965 --> 01:04:05,842
When she got the gift from Aru,

1261
01:04:05,925 --> 01:04:10,096
<i>she complimented him</i>
<i>by calling him a kind person.</i>

1262
01:04:10,179 --> 01:04:12,557
- Then, she rephrased it to "romantic."
- Yeah.

1263
01:04:12,640 --> 01:04:15,226
- I thought that was a great expression.
- I agree.

1264
01:04:15,309 --> 01:04:17,770
The way Mimi uses her words

1265
01:04:17,854 --> 01:04:19,605
is very advanced.

1266
01:04:19,689 --> 01:04:20,523
True.

1267
01:04:20,606 --> 01:04:25,236
<i>- Aru revealed everything he reconned.</i>
<i>- Forget about him.</i>

1268
01:04:25,319 --> 01:04:26,863
"We go down from here."

1269
01:04:27,572 --> 01:04:28,698
Don't show her now.

1270
01:04:28,781 --> 01:04:31,742
- But I think it worked for Mimi.
- Yeah.

1271
01:04:31,826 --> 01:04:33,494
- He got his feelings through.
- Yeah.

1272
01:04:33,578 --> 01:04:36,873
- He showed her how much he likes her.
- Yeah.

1273
01:04:36,956 --> 01:04:38,416
Who knows what could happen?

1274
01:04:38,499 --> 01:04:42,670
Mimi seems like the type
to fall for someone who's devoted to her.

1275
01:04:42,753 --> 01:04:44,255
It's like what we were saying.

1276
01:04:44,338 --> 01:04:47,884
Something could happen
while Atsushi is acting complacent.

1277
01:04:47,967 --> 01:04:49,135
There is a possibility.

1278
01:04:49,218 --> 01:04:54,640
Mimi might fall for his awkward
but sincere nature.

1279
01:04:54,724 --> 01:04:55,850
Yeah.

1280
01:05:16,078 --> 01:05:17,330
Dear Nanami,

1281
01:05:17,413 --> 01:05:20,374
I want to see you again.

1282
01:05:20,458 --> 01:05:23,753
- Nanami?
- Oh!

1283
01:05:23,836 --> 01:05:27,173
- So it's her?
- That's how it is?

1284
01:05:27,256 --> 01:05:28,174
Dear Nanami,

1285
01:05:28,257 --> 01:05:32,803
Please come to Garibaldi Square
at 5:00 p.m. on Day Seven or Day Eight.

1286
01:05:32,887 --> 01:05:35,806
I want to see you again.

1287
01:06:02,541 --> 01:06:04,293
- Hi, Yudai.
- Oh?

1288
01:06:04,794 --> 01:06:06,337
- Hi.
- Hi.

1289
01:06:06,420 --> 01:06:09,048
I'm sorry about today. I had plans.

1290
01:06:09,131 --> 01:06:10,675
Not at all. It's fine.

1291
01:06:10,758 --> 01:06:12,677
- Aren't you cold?
- I'm okay.

1292
01:06:13,302 --> 01:06:14,929
- It's suddenly chilly.
